      • Ticket

        public Ticket()

      • Ticket

        public Ticket(java.lang.String licenseNo,
              java.lang.String state,
              java.lang.String permitNo,
              java.lang.String vehicleModel,
              java.lang.String violation,
              java.lang.String color,
              java.lang.String date,
              java.lang.String time,
              java.lang.String location,
              java.lang.String issuedBy,
              java.lang.String paymentInfo,
              boolean paidticket)
        This is the main constructor where all the ticket data will be stored for one Ticket object. It takes in 12 parameters which are described below.
        Parameters:
        licenseNo - The license number of the vehicle
        state - The state in which the ticket was issued
        permitNo - The permit number of the vehicle
        vehicleModel - The vehicle model brand
        violation - The reason for the ticket being issued
        color - The color of the vehicle
        date - The date when the ticket was issued
        time - The time when the ticket was issued
        location - The location of where the ticket was issued
        issuedBy - The person who issued the ticket
        paymentInfo - The location where payment must be made.
        paidticket - Checks if the ticket was paid or not (true if paid or false if not paid)
